topic: Book Workflow Series ("Nobel laureates explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for obtaining the nobel laureates and the nominees with their relevant attributes
goals.2: Get the number of Italian, French and Iranian winners and check which nation won more awards in the last twenty years.
goals.3: Determine how many Literature nobel laureates have the following contries: Italy, Germany, France, Romania, Denmark, Iran, and China
goals.4: How many Literature Nobel award winners have a PhD (aka Doctorate of Philosophy) (you may check if they have a doctoral advisor)?
goals.5: Are there books from Litarature Nobel Award winners which are not present in the Vatican Library? (if so, who is the author with more books not in the Vatical Library)?

search_workflow.narrative: start your workflow here
search_workflow.query: SELECT COUNT( ?p) WHERE { ?p wdt:P279 wd:Q482980 . }

search_workflow.narrative:
1. Identify the BGP for obtaining the nobel laureates and the nominees with their relevant attributes
To find all the nobel laureates and the nominees we find the node for the Nobel Prize (to analyze it) starting
from the node "Noble Prize in Literature"
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?p ?pname WHERE { wd:Q37922 wdt:P279 ?p . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 50

search_workflow.narrative:
Get wd:Q7191 --> 'Nobel Prize'
Find list of Nobel Prize existing
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?s ?sname WHERE { ?s wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?s <http://schema.org/name> ?sname . } LIMIT 50
output: Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel

search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { ?s ?p wd:Q7191 . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 50

search_workflow.narrative: Return on 'Noble Prize in Literature' we analiyze it to find interesting property
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { ?s ?p wd:Q37922 . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 50

search_workflow.narrative:
Get wdt:P1411 --> predicate 'nominated for' //// wdt:P166 --> predicate 'award received'
Find name - award received/nominated for - type of Noble
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?person ?pn ?ar ?nameNoble WHERE { ?person ?p ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?person <http://schema.org/name> ?pn . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?ar . ?noble <http://schema.org/name> ?nameNoble . FILTER(?p = wdt:P166 || ?p = wdt:P1411 ) } LIMIT 10
output: Edward Grey, 1st Viscount Grey of Fallodon
Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine

search_workflow.narrative:
Get a person IRI random to find its relevant attributes
Get wd:Q57074
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { wd:Q57074 ?p ?o. ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative:
GET:
wdt:P27 --> Country
wdt:P569 --> date of birthday
wdt:P21 --> sex or gender
wdt:P106 --> occupation
Find all noble lauterates and nominees with their relevant attributes relevant
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?person ?pn ?ar ?nameNoble ?countryname ?dateofbirthday ?sexorgender (GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT ?occupation ; separator = ", ") AS ?occupations) WHERE { ?person ?p ?noble . OPTIONAL { ?person wdt:P27 ?country; wdt:P569 ?dateofbirthday ; wdt:P21 ?sog; wdt:P106 ?oc } . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?person <http://schema.org/name> ?pn . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?ar . ?noble <http://schema.org/name> ?nameNoble . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname . ?sog <http://schema.org/name> ?sexorgender . ?oc <http://schema.org/name> ?occupation . FILTER(?p = wdt:P166 || ?p = wdt:P1411 ) } LIMIT 10
output: Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel
actor, author, linguist, playwright, poet, translator, university teacher, writer

search_workflow.narrative:
2. Get the number of Italian, French and Iranian winners and check which nation won more awards in the last twenty years.
Find the IRI for France and Iran, starting from Italy IRI wd:Q38
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?p ?pname WHERE { wd:Q38 wdt:P31 ?p . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative: Get node 'sovereign state' --> wd:Q3624078 to find all the states (its instance of)
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?s ?state WHERE { ?s wdt:P31 wd:Q3624078 . ?s <http://schema.org/name> ?state . } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative: Look for France and Iran
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?s ?state WHERE { ?s wdt:P31 wd:Q3624078 . ?s <http://schema.org/name> ?state . FILTER (REGEX(?state, "rance") || REGEX(?state, "ran")) } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative:
Get node 'France' --> wd:Q142
Get node 'Iran' --> wd:Q794
To find all the Noble winners we use the predicate found above 'award received' --> wdt:P166
Try for italian winners
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?winner ?winnername ?ar ?noblename ?countryname WHERE { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q38 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?winner <http://schema.org/name> ?winnername . wdt:P166 <http://schema.org/name> ?ar . ?noble <http://schema.org/name> ?noblename . wd:Q38 <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname . } LIMIT 100
output: Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel

search_workflow.narrative: Find the numbers of italian, french and iranian winners
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?italianwinners ?frenchwinners ?iranianwinners WHERE { { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?italianwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q38 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?frenchwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q142 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?iranianwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q794 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } } LIMIT 100

3. Determine how many Literature nobel laureates have the following contries: Italy, Germany, France, Romania, Denmark,
Iran, and China
We have to find the IRI for Germany, Romania, Denmark, China
We have found above the following:
Italy --> wd:Q38
France --> wd:Q142
Iran --> wd:Q794
We look now for: Germany, Romania, Denmark, China --> searching on Sovereign state
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?s ?state WHERE { ?s wdt:P31 wd:Q3624078 . ?s <http://schema.org/name> ?state . FILTER (REGEX(?state, "erman") || REGEX(?state, "omani") || REGEX(?state, "enmark") || REGEX(?state, "hina")) } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative:
GET:
Germany --> wd:Q183
Romania --> wd:Q218
Denmark --> wd:Q35
China --> wd:Q148
Find now the number of Literature Nobel lauraeates have all the countries
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?italianwinners ?frenchwinners ?iranianwinners ?germanywinners ?romanianwinners ?chinawinners WHERE { { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?italianwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q38 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?frenchwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q142 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?iranianwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q794 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?germanywinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q183 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?romanianwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q218 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?denmarkwinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q35 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } { select distinct (COUNT(?winner) AS ?chinawinners) { ?winner wdt:P27 wd:Q148 . ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . } } } LIMIT 100

FILTER(?noble = wd:Q37922) } LIMIT 100

(if so, who is the author with more books not in the Vatical Library)?
I try to find something that won an award
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?winner ?winnername ?ar ?noblename WHERE { ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble ; wdt:P31 ?og . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?winner <http://schema.org/name> ?winnername . wdt:P166 <http://schema.org/name> ?ar . ?noble <http://schema.org/name> ?noblename . search_workflow.narrative: But I understand that I have to find book.. so I look for instance to find book
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?og ?ogname WHERE { ?winner wdt:P31 ?og . ?winner <http://schema.org/name> ?winnername . ?og <http://schema.org/name> ?ogname . } LIMIT 10

search_workflow.narrative: Look for 'Book'
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?og ?ogname WHERE { ?winner wdt:P31 ?og . ?winner <http://schema.org/name> ?winnername . ?og <http://schema.org/name> ?ogname . FILTER regex(?ogname, "\\bbook\\b", "i") } LIMIT 10

I look only for books that won Noble in Literature
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?winner ?winnername ?ar ?noblename WHERE { ?winner wdt:P166 ?noble ; wdt:P279 wd:Q571 . ?noble wdt:P279 wd:Q7191 . ?winner <http://schema.org/name> ?winnername . wdt:P166 <http://schema.org/name> ?ar . ?noble <http://schema.org/name> ?noblename . } LIMIT 10
